2. DATA — Open Government Licence v3.0 and third-party terms
================================================================================

Applies to: the figures in data/.

Most figures in this repository are derived from UK public sector information
licensed under the Open Government Licence v3.0:

    Contains public sector information licensed under the Open Government
    Licence v3.0.
    http://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/doc/open-government-licence/version/3/

This covers material published by the Office for National Statistics, the Home
Office, the National Audit Office, the Office for Budget Responsibility, the
Migration Advisory Committee, HM Courts and Tribunals Service and the House of
Commons Library (the last under the Open Parliament Licence, whose terms are
materially equivalent for this use).

Figures sourced from the Migration Observatory (University of Oxford) and
Skills for Care are not Crown copyright and are reproduced here as short
factual extracts with attribution. Their own terms apply; check the source
before redistributing those figures in bulk.

Attribution is recorded per figure: every metric in data/ carries source_name,
source_url and published_date. If you reuse these files, keep that metadata
attached. Stripping the source metadata from these figures defeats the purpose
of the project and breaches the attribution requirement above.
